@inject IJSRuntime JSRuntime

<section class="bg-slate-50 dark:bg-[#0B1221] py-24 relative overflow-hidden" id="tribal-analysis">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <!-- Header -->
        <div class="mb-16 text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto">
            <span class="text-orange-600 font-bold tracking-wider uppercase text-sm">Legal Fact Check</span>
            <h2 class="mt-2 text-3xl font-black tracking-tight text-slate-900 dark:text-white sm:text-4xl">
                THE "TRIBAL THREAT" <span class="text-orange-600">DECEPTION</span>
            </h2>
            <p class="mt-4 text-xl italic text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 font-medium max-w-2xl mx-auto">
                Mayor Tucker and Senator Busch claim a "Tribal Casino" is inevitable if their commercial one isn't
                approved.
                Federal law indicates this is a <strong>manufactured lie</strong> designed to panic State House and
                Senate voters and justify their agenda.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Intro Card -->
        <div
            class="bg-white dark:bg-surface-dark border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 rounded-3xl p-8 shadow-lg mb-12">
            <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 items-center">
                <div
                    class="shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center size-16 rounded-full bg-orange-100 dark:bg-orange-900/30 text-orange-600">
                    <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-3xl">warning</span>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2">"Fritz Road" Scare Tactic</h3>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
                        The administration argues that the Miami Tribe of Oklahoma will open a tax-free casino
                        on their Fritz Road land if we don't act. A textualist analysis of the <a
                            href="https://www.nigc.gov/office-of-general-counsel/laws-and-regulations/indian-gaming-regulatory-act/"
                            target="_blank" class="underline hover:text-blue-500 transition-colors font-bold">Indian
                            Gaming Regulatory Act (IGRA)</a> shows three formidable legal walls blocking
                        this path.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- The 3 Legal Walls Grid -->
        <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 mb-12 items-start">

            <!-- Card 1 -->
            <div
                class="bg-white dark:bg-surface-dark p-8 rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 relative group hover:border-orange-500/50 transition-colors shadow-lg">
                <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 p-6 opacity-10 group-hover:opacity-20 transition-opacity">
                    <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-8xl text-slate-900 dark:text-white">event_busy</span>
                </div>
                <span
                    class="inline-block px-3 py-1 bg-primary text-white text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider rounded-full mb-6">Wall
                    #1</span>
                <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-4">1988 Cutoff</h4>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
                    IGRA prohibits gaming on land acquired after Oct 1988. The Fritz Road land was acquired
                    in <strong>June 2024</strong>—nearly 36 years too late. It is presumptively ineligible.
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Card 2 -->
            <div
                class="bg-white dark:bg-surface-dark p-8 rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 relative group hover:border-orange-500/50 transition-colors shadow-lg">
                <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 p-6 opacity-10 group-hover:opacity-20 transition-opacity">
                    <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-8xl text-slate-900 dark:text-white">history</span>
                </div>
                <span
                    class="inline-block px-3 py-1 bg-primary text-white text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider rounded-full mb-6">Wall
                    #2</span>
                <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-4">86-Year Gap</h4>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
                    Exceptions require a "temporal connection." The Miami Tribe was recognized in 1938.
                    Acquiring land 86 years later fails this test. It is not an open-ended license.
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Card 3 -->
            <div
                class="bg-white dark:bg-surface-dark p-8 rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 relative group hover:border-orange-500/50 transition-colors shadow-lg">
                <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 p-6 opacity-10 group-hover:opacity-20 transition-opacity">
                    <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-8xl text-slate-900 dark:text-white">gavel</span>
                </div>
                <span
                    class="inline-block px-3 py-1 bg-primary text-white text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider rounded-full mb-6">Wall
                    #3</span>
                <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-4">Governor's Veto</h4>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
                    The only remaining path requires the <strong>Governor's Concurrence</strong>. No Indiana
                    Governor would approve a tax-free competitor to state casinos. It is a political dead
                    end.
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Image/Text (Spanning Row 2 and 3 of Col 2) -->
            <div class="space-y-4 h-full flex flex-col justify-center row-span-2">
                <div class="relative rounded-3xl overflow-hidden shadow-2xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 cursor-pointer group"
                    onclick="window.openImageModal('assets/THE_TRIBE_IS_COMING_POLITICAL_CARTOON.png')">
                    <img src="assets/THE_TRIBE_IS_COMING_POLITICAL_CARTOON.png"
                        alt="Political Cartoon: The Tribe is Coming"
                        class="w-full h-auto block transition-transform duration-500 group-hover:scale-105"
                        loading="lazy" />
                </div>
                <p class="text-center italic text-sm text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 font-medium px-4">
                    State Senator Justin Busch and Mayor Sharon Tucker work with WFFT FOX 55 Fort Wayne to 
                    manufactures urgency and help justify bypassing a voter referendum, as teenagers casually play frisbee on the Fritz Road property in the background.
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Verdict (Moved to Col 1, Row 3) -->
            <div
                class="bg-white dark:bg-surface-dark rounded-3xl p-8 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 shadow-lg h-full flex flex-col justify-center">
                <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 items-center">
                    <div
                        class="shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center size-16 rounded-full bg-emerald-100 dark:bg-emerald-900/30 text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-500">
                        <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-3xl">gavel</span>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Verdict</h3>
                        <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
                            The Miami Tribe's land is for a Cultural Resources Extension Office (CREO), not a
                            casino.
                            The "Tribal Option" is not a legal reality—it is a <strong>rhetorical strategy designed to
                                manufacture urgency.</strong>
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Legislative Analysis / Referendum Gap -->
        <div class="mb-16">
            <div
                class="bg-white dark:bg-surface-dark rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 overflow-hidden shadow-lg">

                <!-- Header inside the card -->
                <div class="p-8 pb-4">
                    <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
                        <div class="p-3 bg-red-100 dark:bg-red-900/30 rounded-xl text-red-600 dark:text-red-500">
                            <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-3xl">how_to_vote</span>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">Their Real Agenda:
                                Avoiding a
                                Public Vote</h3>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-base">Why characterize the tribe as an
                                existential threat? To bypass democracy.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div
                    class="grid lg:grid-cols-3 divide-y lg:divide-y-0 lg:divide-x divide-slate-200 dark:divide-slate-600 border-t border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800">

                    <!-- Col 1: The Vehicle -->
                    <div class="p-8">
                        <h4
                            class="font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-4 flex items-center gap-2 text-base uppercase tracking-wider">
                            <span class="text-orange-500">01.</span> Vehicle
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-base text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
                            <strong class="text-slate-900 dark:text-white">House Bill 1038</strong> (New License)
                            and <strong class="text-slate-900 dark:text-white">Senate Bill 70</strong> (Relocation)
                            are the current mechanisms. Crucially, Mayor Tucker has refused to guarantee a binding
                            local referendum.
                        </p>
                        <div
                            class="bg-orange-50 dark:bg-orange-900/20 p-4 rounded-xl border border-orange-100 dark:border-orange-500/20">
                            <span
                                class="text-base font-bold text-orange-700 dark:text-orange-400 uppercase tracking-wide block mb-1">Democratic
                                Deficit</span>
                            <p class="text-base text-orange-900 dark:text-orange-200 leading-relaxed">
                                Allowing a few officials—one of whom was not elected by her constituents, but
                                appointed by a caucus of Democrats—to fundamentally alter the city's character
                                disenfranchises the voters who bear the costs.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Col 2: The Precedent -->
                    <div class="p-8">
                        <h4
                            class="font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-4 flex items-center gap-2 text-base uppercase tracking-wider">
                            <span class="text-blue-500">02.</span> Historical Precedent
                        </h4>
                        <div class="space-y-6">
                            <div>
                                <div class="flex justify-between items-center mb-1">
                                    <span class="text-base font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">1993 Riverboat
                                        Act</span>
                                    <span
                                        class="text-base font-bold text-emerald-600 bg-emerald-100 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">VOTE
                                        REQUIRED</span>
                                </div>
                                <p class="text-base text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">Citizens in Evansville,
                                    Hammond, and Lawrenceburg <em
                                        class="text-slate-900 dark:text-white font-medium">voted Yes</em>
                                    before
                                    licenses were issued.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="w-full h-px bg-slate-200 dark:bg-slate-800"></div>
                            <div>
                                <div class="flex justify-between items-center mb-1">
                                    <span class="text-base font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">2019 Terre
                                        Haute</span>
                                    <span
                                        class="text-base font-bold text-emerald-600 bg-emerald-100 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">VOTE
                                        REQUIRED</span>
                                </div>
                                <p class="text-base text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">Moving a license to a new
                                    community explicitly required a referendum (63% approval).</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Col 3: The Deviation -->
                    <div class="p-8 bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-800/50">
                        <h4
                            class="font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-4 flex items-center gap-2 text-base uppercase tracking-wider">
                            <span class="text-red-500">03.</span> Deviation
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-base text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
                            Bypassing a referendum for Fort Wayne is a <strong
                                class="text-red-600 dark:text-red-500">radical
                                deviation</strong> from the standard set by the 1993 Act and 2019 Gaming Bill.
                        </p>
                        <p
                            class="text-base font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white italic relative pl-4 border-l-2 border-red-500 bg-red-50 dark:bg-red-900/20 p-4 rounded-xl">
                            "Bypassing this step suggests a fear that the community—if fully informed of the social
                            costs—would reject the proposal."
                        </p>
                    </div>

                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Conclusion -->

        <!-- Public Sentiment Section -->
        <div class="mb-16">
            <div
                class="bg-white dark:bg-surface-dark rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 shadow-lg overflow-hidden">

                <!-- Header & Explanation inside the card -->
                <div class="p-8 pb-0">
                    <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
                        <div
                            class="p-3 bg-blue-100 dark:bg-blue-900/30 rounded-xl text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-500">
                            <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-3xl">psychology</span>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">Why The Rush? Hint:
                                "Education Gap"</h3>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-base">
                                Data shows that the more voters learn, the more they oppose it.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed mb-8">
                        While the <a href="https://naaig.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/IN_iGaming_Memo_final.pdf"
                            target="_blank" class="underline hover:text-blue-500 transition-colors">referenced
                            poll</a> focused on iGaming (online gambling), the underlying
                        concerns—24/7 availability, addiction, economic loss, and social harm—shared by
                        respondents are transferable to the debate over a physical casino in Fort Wayne. The
                        data reveals that resistance is not just a fringe position but a majority consensus.
                        <strong class="text-slate-900 dark:text-white">SaveFW believes that, if given time to
                            better inform residents, local polls would likely indicate the overwhelming majority of
                            Allen County residents opposes the
                            casino.</strong>
                    </p>
                </div>

                <!-- Top: The Education Gap Visual -->
                <div class="p-8 border-b border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 pt-0">
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider text-base">
                        2025
                        Statewide Poll Results</h4>

                    <!-- Progress Bar Style Comparison -->
                    <div class="space-y-8">
                        <!-- Stage 1 -->
                        <div>
                            <div class="flex justify-between text-base mb-2">
                                <span class="font-medium text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">Initial Opposition
                                    (Uninformed)</span>
                                <span class="font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">19%</span>
                            </div>
                            <div
                                class="w-full bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-900 rounded-full h-4 border border-slate-200">
                                <div class="bg-slate-400 h-4 rounded-full" style="width: 19%"></div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <!-- Stage 2 -->
                        <div>
                            <div class="flex justify-between text-base mb-2">
                                <span class="font-medium text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">After Hearing "We're
                                    Open 24/7"</span>
                                <span class="font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">58%</span>
                            </div>
                            <div
                                class="w-full bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-900 rounded-full h-4 border border-slate-200">
                                <div class="bg-orange-500 h-4 rounded-full" style="width: 58%"></div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <!-- Stage 3 -->
                        <div>
                            <div class="flex justify-between text-base mb-2">
                                <span class="font-bold text-red-600 dark:text-red-500">Informed Opposition (Economic
                                    & Social Costs)</span>
                                <span class="font-bold text-red-600 dark:text-red-500">67%</span>
                            </div>
                            <div
                                class="w-full bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-900 rounded-full h-4 relative border border-slate-200">
                                <!-- Striped pattern or animation -->
                                <div class="bg-red-600 h-4 rounded-full" style="width: 67%"></div>
                            </div>
                            <p class="mt-2 text-base text-slate-500 italic">Source: <a
                                    href="https://naaig.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/IN_iGaming_Memo_final.pdf"
                                    target="_blank" class="underline hover:text-blue-500 transition-colors">Pantheon
                                    Insight / NAAiG Poll (2025)</a></p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Demographic Breakdown Grid -->
                <div
                    class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-5 divide-y md:divide-y-0 md:divide-x divide-slate-200 dark:divide-slate-800 bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-900/50">
                    <!-- Seniors -->
                    <div class="p-6 text-center">
                        <span class="block text-3xl font-black text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-1">82%</span>
                        <span class="text-base font-bold text-slate-500 uppercase">Seniors (65+)</span>
                        <p class="text-base text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mt-2 leading-tight">Targeted by
                            daytime marketing
                            schemes.</p>
                    </div>
                    <!-- Women -->
                    <div class="p-6 text-center">
                        <span class="block text-3xl font-black text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-1">72%</span>
                        <span class="text-base font-bold text-slate-500 uppercase">Women</span>
                        <p class="text-base text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mt-2 leading-tight">Cite concerns
                            over family
                            stability.</p>
                    </div>
                    <!-- Grads -->
                    <div class="p-6 text-center">
                        <span class="block text-3xl font-black text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-1">72%</span>
                        <span class="text-base font-bold text-slate-500 uppercase">College Grads</span>
                        <p class="text-base text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mt-2 leading-tight">Understand
                            economic "substitution
                            effects."</p>
                    </div>
                    <!-- GOP -->
                    <div class="p-6 text-center">
                        <span class="block text-3xl font-black text-red-600 dark:text-red-500 mb-1">68%</span>
                        <span class="text-base font-bold text-slate-500 uppercase">Republicans</span>
                        <p class="text-base text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mt-2 leading-tight">Fiscal
                            responsibility values.</p>
                    </div>
                    <!-- Dems -->
                    <div class="p-6 text-center">
                        <span class="block text-3xl font-black text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-500 mb-1">70%</span>
                        <span class="text-base font-bold text-slate-500 uppercase">Democrats</span>
                        <p class="text-base text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mt-2 leading-tight">Predatory
                            practices on the poor.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Bottom Banner -->
                <div
                    class="p-6 bg-white dark:bg-slate-900 text-center border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800">
                    <p class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
                        <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-lg align-text-bottom mr-1">campaign</span>
                        This "silent majority" explains why officials are bypassing a referendum. They know they
                        would lose.
                    </p>
                </div>

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="w-full relative shadow-2xl">
    <img src="assets/depressing_downtown.png" alt="Impact on Downtown" class="w-full h-auto block" loading="lazy">
    <div
        class="absolute inset-y-0 left-0 w-full flex flex-col justify-center pl-8 sm:pl-12 lg:pl-16 z-20 pointer-events-none">
        <h2
            class="text-3xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-7xl font-black text-white leading-[0.9] tracking-tighter drop-shadow-lg">
            <span
                class="block opacity-0 translate-y-8 transition-all duration-700 ease-out scroll-reveal delay-0">FORT
                WAYNE</span>
            <span
                class="block opacity-0 translate-y-8 transition-all duration-700 ease-out scroll-reveal delay-300 text-orange-500">DESERVES</span>
            <span
                class="block opacity-0 translate-y-8 transition-all duration-700 ease-out scroll-reveal delay-600">BETTER</span>
        </h2>
    </div>
</section>

@code {
    protected override async Task OnAfterRenderAsync(bool firstRender)
    {
        if (firstRender)
        {
            await JSRuntime.InvokeVoidAsync("window.initScrollReveal");
        }
    }
}
